# Folder Structure Guidelines

## Root Layout

```bash
/src
  /app
    layout.tsx      # Root layout
    page.tsx        # Home page
    /api            # API route handlers
    /dashboard      # App route segment
  /components       # Reusable UI and feature components
  /lib              # Utility functions, helpers, and API clients
  /styles           # Tailwind/CSS modules if needed
  /middleware       # Vercel middleware handlers
/public             # Static assets (images, icons, etc.)
```

## Component Placement

* Shared UI: `/components/ui`
* Layout-related: `/components/layout`
* Forms: `/components/forms`
* Route-specific private components: `_components` inside the relevant route folder

## App Folder Usage

* Use `/app/layout.tsx` for global layout
* Use `/app/error.tsx` and `/app/loading.tsx` where appropriate
* Use `route.ts` inside `/app/api/` for route handlers

## Benefits

* Clear separation of concerns
* Easier navigation and onboarding
* Scalable as the application grows
* Aligns with Next.js App Router conventions
